          <h2>Best Cashback Credit Cards in India</h2>
          <p>Cashback credit cards are the simplest way to earn returns on your spending — there's no points to track, no complicated redemption process, and no expiry worries. When you make a purchase, a percentage of the transaction amount is automatically credited back to your statement as cashback. This makes cashback cards ideal for people who want straightforward, guaranteed savings on their everyday expenses.</p>
          <p>The best cashback cards in India for 2026 offer between 1.5% to 5% returns depending on the spending category. Some cards offer flat cashback on all spends (uniform rate regardless of where you shop), while others offer accelerated cashback on specific categories like groceries, fuel, online shopping, or dining. Choose based on where you spend the most.</p>

          <h2>Key Features of Cashback Credit Cards</h2>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Flat Cashback:</strong> Earn 1-2% cashback on all spends regardless of category — perfect for varied spending patterns</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Category Cashback:</strong> Get 5% cashback on specific categories like online shopping, groceries, or dining</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Auto Statement Credit:</strong> Cashback is automatically adjusted against your next credit card bill — no manual redemption needed</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>No Minimum Spend:</strong> Most cashback cards start earning from the first rupee with no minimum transaction requirements</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Transparent Returns:</strong> Know exactly how much you're saving — no guessing the value of reward points</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Additional Perks:</strong> Many cashback cards also offer fuel surcharge waivers, EMI conversions, and insurance benefits</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Top 5 Cashback Credit Cards for 2026</h2>
          <p>Compare the best cashback cards based on return rates, monthly caps, and overall value.</p>

          <table class="rate-table">
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Card Name</th><th>Annual Fee</th><th>Cashback Rate</th><th>Key Benefits</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>SBI Cashback</strong></td><td>₹999</td><td>5% on online spends</td><td>₹25,000 annual cashback cap, fuel surcharge waiver</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>HDFC Millennia</strong></td><td>₹1,000</td><td>5% on Amazon/Flipkart</td><td>1% on all offline spends, SmartBuy offers, lounge access</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Axis ACE</strong></td><td>Nil</td><td>5% on bills, 2% on all</td><td>Lifetime free, Google Pay cashback, no upper cap restriction</td></tr>
