            </tbody>
          </table>

          <h2>Eligibility for Cashback Credit Cards</h2>
          <p>Cashback cards are widely accessible. Here are the typical requirements:</p>

          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Age:</strong> 21-60 years (salaried) or 21-65 years (self-employed and business owners)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Income:</strong> ₹15,000-₹25,000/month minimum depending on the card tier; lifetime free cards often have lower thresholds</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Credit Score:</strong> 700+ for most cashback cards; some basic cashback cards accept 650+ CIBIL scores</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Employment:</strong> Salaried, self-employed, business owners, and even students (for select co-branded cards)</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Existing Cards:</strong> Having an existing card with good payment history improves approval chances for premium cashback cards</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Documents:</strong> PAN Card, Aadhaar, income proof (salary slips or ITR), and recent bank statements</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>How to Apply for a Cashback Credit Card</h3>
